  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to NOGAMU systems</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="SV">Support to NOGAMU systems</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kisaka &amp; Company has applied to Sida for funding of 720,000 SEK to carry out the &quot;Review of the Internal Control Systems of NOGAMU&quot; during the period February to August 2014. 

The objective of the assignment is to support NOGAMU in implementating of the systems and compliance review recommendations to ensure proper functioning of the financial management and Programme/project reporting systems. It will specifically involve; review of the control environment to identify potential risks, a review of the relevancy, adequacy and reliability of the internal control systems, organizational structure and program performance of NOGAMU, a review of the progress made in accordance with the systems review recommendations and Provision of an agreeable plan for continued support to NOGAMU. 

Kisaka &amp; Company undertake the assignment as part of the Framework agreement on audit support to the Embassy.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="SV">PLEASE REVIEW YOUR ANSWER AS THE QUESTION HAS BEEN CHANGED

Insatsen genomf&#xF6;rs av Kisaka &amp; Company som avropas inom ramen f&#xF6;r ambassadens ramavtal med firman att tillhandah&#xE5;lla revisionstj&#xE4;nster. Kontraktskostnaden uppg&#xE5;r till 720 000 kr f&#xF6;r arvoden och omkostnader. Uppdraget kommer att delas upp i tv&#xE5; delar. Den f&#xF6;rsta avser att granska statusen f&#xF6;r ekonomisk efterlevnad och f&#xF6;rvaltning och den andra att st&#xF6;dja NOGAMU att genomf&#xF6;ra rekommendationerna fr&#xE5;n tidigare genomf&#xF6;rd systemrevision under en sexm&#xE5;nadersperiod. Uppdraget syftar till att identifiera potentiella risker , relevans&#xF6;versyn, l&#xE4;mplighet och tillf&#xF6;rlitlighet i interna kontrollsystem, organisationsstruktur, NOGAMUs kapacitet avseende genomf&#xF6;rda program samt en &#xF6;versyn av de framsteg som gjorts i enlighet med systemrevisionens rekommendationer, inkl. &#xE5;tg&#xE4;rdsplan f&#xF6;r fortsatt st&#xF6;d till NOGAMU .</narrative>
  </description>
